National women&rsquo;s football team, Harambee Starlets battle visiting Cameroon&rsquo;s Indomitable Lionesses today in an International friendly at the Safaricom Stadium, Kasarani.Both team are using the encounter as a build-up for the forthcoming Africa women&rsquo;s Cup of Nation (AWCON) final to be held between November 19 and December 3 in Limbe City of Cameroon.The match kicks off at 4pm and gates will open from 10am and ticketing will be sold at the same venue at a cost of Sh100.In a press statement, Football Kenya Federation (FKF) said for the first time they have incorporated entertainment to spice up the occasion. Refreshments, the statement said will also be sold by selected vendors.The press statement read in part: &ldquo;In an effort aimed at creating prestige and awe during the fixture, FKF has for the first time incorporated entertainment and refreshments to be sold by select vendors at the match venue, with an after party also on the programme.&rdquo;Starlet are drawn in Pool &lsquo;B&rsquo; alongside title holders Nigeria, Ghana and Mali while their opponents today are in Pool &lsquo;A&rsquo; together with hosts Cameroon, Egypt, Zimbabwe and South Africa. After the friendly tie today against Cameroon, the Kenyan side will play Egypt on October 28 before finally taking on Cameroon in a return leg on November 5 away.